blog.name: momentsinreading
blog.title: Intellectual Wallpaper
blog.description:
I've been collecting quotes and passages I liked for over fifteen years. You can see my progression as a person and my changing interests as they go along. I decided to put them out there for the Internet to see so it's not just me enjoying them. Some are from pop culture, some from authors, podcasts and journalists, some are even from my family and friends. I hope you find something useful, inspirational, moving, amusing, weird- or all of the above.


If you want you can check out my personal Tumblr at piratelawyer.tumblr.com. It's about as random as this.

summary: brielarson I met Agnès Varda on October 12th, 2017. I interviewed her for a Q and A at the @sidgrauman. Before it, we had dinner...
caption: brielarson I met Agnès Varda on October 12th, 2017. I interviewed her for a Q and A at the @sidgrauman. Before it, we had dinner in one of the empty theaters with her daughter Rosalie. The first thing she said to me was “I’m a soup freak” - then we talked about her life during the French new wave, representation, consumption, and family. I saw Cleo from 5 to 7 when I was 16 and it changed my world. It’s impossible to quantify how she impacted cinema, the female gaze, and women across the globe. Today should be an international holiday. Thank you Agnès. I encourage everyone to dedicate some time to this woman’s work and voice today. It’s unmatched. Love to her friends and family.
